    <h3>Step 2: Plan</h3>
    <p class="summary">Set up your compost bin&hellip;</p>
    <div class="action--description">
      <p>Work with your cafeteria staff to set up collection bins. Make sure you make clear signs that indicate what can and can’t go into the bins. Things that are ok include food and vegetable scraps, paper, egg shells, tea bags, bread, nut shells, and food-soiled cardboard. Things to avoid include meat and fish scraps, cheese and dairy products, plastics and greasy foods.</p>

      <p>Then pick a location for your compost pile where you will dump the bins out every day. Select a dry, shady spot near a hose. You can either use a plastic container or fence off an area with wooden boards. Your pile should be about 3 cubic feet.</p>

      <p class="action--result">
        You chose to send your socks to <strong class="js-action-result">The Evil Lair</strong>. (<a class="js-change-location" href="#">change</a>)
